<h2 id="pmcpontine-micturition-center-barringtons-nucleus">PMC(Pontine Micturition Center, Barrington’s nucleus)</h2>

<p><img src="C:\Blog\_posts\2019-03-07-urine-control-neuroscience.assets\1551948145591.png" alt="1551948145591" /></p>

<p>Two types of neurons:</p>

<ul>
  <li>(crh)expressing corticotropin-releasing hormone — bladder-contracting preganglionic
neurons – bladder pressure</li>
  <li>(esr1)expressing estrogen receptors — sphincter-relaxing interneurons in the spinal cord – bladder contraction and relaxation of urethral sphincter</li>
</ul>

